Top music executive, Don Jazzy, has said that men should “go learn how to toast” women. The Mavin Records boss stated this on his verified Instagram handle, where he said that a lot of women have all the money men normally use as tools to get their attention. Don Jazzy, whose real name is Michael Collins Ajereh, has been a butt of jokes and memes about his bachelorhood. He had also reportedly informed his fans through a throwback post that he had once being divorced when he was much younger, and that he is now taking his time. Don Jazzy became a popular brand when he teamed up with D’banj to form the MoHit records. He worked with Wande Coal, Dr Sid, Tiwa Savage and Ice Prince to bring to the music scene new pop flavours. After the disolution he formed Mavin records and became a social media influencer. Mavin records has also brought to the fore an array of international stars, Rema, Ayra Starr, Crayon, Ladipoe, Jonny Drille and others. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com